WORLD FAMOUS FORT MYERS BEACH SHRIMP FESTIVAL
The Fort Myers Beach Shrimp Festival is put on by the Fort Myers Beach Lions Club and raises tens of thousands of dollars for charities like local eye surgeries and eye cases, scholarships for area students, Florida Lions Eye Bank, Southeast Guide Dogs, large print books for the local library, little league and youth soccer, Beach Elementary and Cypress Lakes High School student needs.
Watch the Parade
Eat Delicious Food
Meet the Queen
Shop Shrimp Festival
About the Fort Myers Beach Lions Club

People's Choice
The Shrimp Festival Queen’s Pageant is collecting votes for the title of ‘People’s Choice.’ The princess who collects the most votes in the form of donations will win the title of People’s Choice. Each donation goes directly back into the community of those in need. Cast your vote by entering how many votes you’d like to cast in the form of donation dollars in the box below. Make sure to enter your contestants name in the field provided when checking out and submitting payment.
VOTING WILL CLOSE ON THE NIGHT BEFORE THE PAGEANT.
ALL VOTES MOST BE IN BY THEN
.
Good Luck To ALL Of Our Princesses!
